# Testing Rules

## What to Test
- Every service function: unit test with mocked Prisma.
- Every utility function: unit test with pure inputs/outputs.
- Every API endpoint: integration test with supertest and a test database.
- Every React component that contains logic: unit test with React Testing Library.
- Every custom hook: unit test with renderHook.
- Do NOT test: shadcn/ui components, pure presentational components with no logic, Next.js routing internals.

## Test Structure
- Arrange-Act-Assert pattern. Every test has exactly 3 sections with a blank line between them.
- One assertion per test. If testing multiple behaviors, write multiple tests.
- Test file co-located with the implementation: `booking.service.test.ts` next to `booking.service.ts`.
- Test names follow: `describe('ServiceName', () => { it('should [expected behavior] when [condition]', ...) })`.
- No shared mutable state between tests. Each test sets up its own fixtures.

## Mocking Rules
- Mock at the boundary: mock Prisma client, mock external API calls, mock email sends.
- Never mock internal functions of the unit under test.
- Use vitest's `vi.mock()` for module mocking.
- Create typed mock factories in `tests/factories/` for all Prisma models.

## Coverage Targets
- Services: 90% line coverage minimum.
- Utils: 100% line coverage.
- Controllers: 80% line coverage via integration tests.
- Frontend hooks: 80% line coverage.
- Run coverage check in CI. Fail build if targets are not met.
